text.section:
A substance is listed in Schedule V if the substance includes a compound, mixture, or preparation that contains the following quantities of narcotic drugs or their salts:
not more than 200 milligrams of codeine per 100 milliliters or per 100 grams;
not more than 100 milligrams of dihydrocodeine per 100 milliliters or per 100 grams;
not more than 50 milligrams of ethylmorphine per 100 milliliters or per 100 grams;
not more than 2.5 milligrams of diphenoxylate and not less than 25 micrograms of atropine sulfate per dosage unit; or
unless specifically excepted under this subtitle, or unless listed in another schedule, any material, compound, mixture, or preparation containing buprenorphine or its salt; and
nonnarcotic active medicinal ingredients in sufficient proportion to confer on the compound, mixture, or preparation valuable medicinal qualities other than those possessed by the narcotic drug alone.
